Heatmap for DEG: complex heatmap

RuiLi

06/18/2019

Communications

  • Visualized with Zscore
  • Only significant Differentially Expressed Genes (DEG) from WT:TRT_VS_UNT included
  • MUT-TRT and MUT-UNT also plotted to see the difference in expression change

Code log:

  • Use zscore for each gene scaled among samples for visualization
  • Drop rows with duplicated gene_names and print out which rows are dropped

colnames(df) = c("gene_id", "baseMean", "log2FoldChange", "lfcSE", "pvalue", 'padj', "FC", "Name", "GO", "description", "MUT_TRT1", "MUT_TRT2", "MUT_UNT1" ,             "MUT_UNT2" ,                 "WT_TRT1",
"WT_TRT2"  ,                 "WT_UNT1"    ,               "WT_UNT2"  )

# sort by LFC
df <- df[order(df$log2FoldChange), ]
exp_idx <- c(11:18)

# remove duplicated gene names
df.duplicated <- df[duplicated(df$Name),]
print("duplicated gene names")

exp_df.sig <- df.sig[, exp_idx]

Heatmap for DEG

## [1] NA NA

Heatmap Complete Hierarchical Clustering by Manhattan Distance

  • Used Z-score for clustering and visualization
  • Z-score calculated from TPM for each gene, scaled among samples

Hide gene names

Heatmap(num_df, 
        column_title = outname,
        row_title = paste(num_sig, 'DEG'),
        name = 'Z-score',
        
        cluster_rows = T,
        cluster_columns = F, 
        clustering_distance_rows = "manhattan",
        clustering_method_rows = 'complete', 
        
        show_row_names = F,
        show_column_names = T,
        
        show_row_dend = T, 
        show_column_dend = T,
        
        top_annotation = ha, 
        
        col = colorRamp2(c(min_exp, 0, max_exp), 
                         c("blue", 'white',  "red")), 
        fontsize(4)
        ) + 
rowAnnotation(
    link = row_anno_link(at = marker_idx, labels = markers),
    width = unit(5, "mm") + max_text_width(markers))
